# Demo safety (Field Engineer)

When running or preparing **customer demos** in this repo:

- Use `./scripts/demos/setup.sh` and `./scripts/demos/reset.sh` — do not invent one-off git teardown.
- Keep demo work on local `demo/<id>` branches only unless the user asks to push.
- Never force-push `main` / `master`. Never delete remote branches unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer small, reversible UI/copy changes during live demos; avoid auth, billing, migrations, and alert-evaluation core.
- After a session, reset before starting another demo so the next customer starts clean.
- If `.demo-state` exists, treat a demo as active — confirm before switching contexts.
- Do not use `git clean -fd` / `--clean-untracked` unless the user explicitly asks.
